name: src/submodules/Position.js
Position
description:
Implementation of rfc7946 (GeoJSON) Section 3.1.1

A position is an abstract, list-like structure
conatining coordinates or other position objects.
A Position can represent the coordinates attribute
of any GeoJSON geometry object.

name: constructor
description: Initializes the array, ignores all arguments.

name: add
description: Adds a coordinate or position at an optionally provided position index.

params.name: (Number)
params.description: [position] Index of the position object to add it to.

throws.description: If coordinate argument is not a valid type.

name: remove
description: Removes the first instance found of the provided Coordinate or Position.

name: at
description: Access the element at the provided index.

name: has
description: Checks if the provided element is in this Position.

return.description: Whether the element is in this Position.

name: size
description:
Get the Number of elements in this Position.
This is a one-dimensional search
and does not count sub-position coordinates or positions

name: equals
description:
Check equality of this position and another position.
Compares all coordinates and sub-coordinates.

unknown.tagValue: {boolean} True if all coordinates and sub-coordinates are equal.

return.description: True if all coordinates and sub-coordinates are equal.
